WEBVTT

00:02.667 --> 00:05.167
[ Wind Whistling ]

00:07.000 --> 00:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:24.900 --> 00:27.967
[ Dog Barking ]

00:46.733 --> 00:49.933
[ Man ]
Goosebumps.

00:51.500 --> 00:53.667
Viewer beware.

00:54.100 --> 00:56.600
You're in for a scare.

00:56.600 --> 00:58.600
[ Chuckles ]

01:01.600 --> 01:03.600
[ Coach ]
Lay it!

01:06.100 --> 01:09.167
Get with it, Judith.
Come on.

01:09.167 --> 01:10.467
[ Girl ]
Let's go!

01:11.933 --> 01:14.733
[ Cheering ]

01:17.333 --> 01:19.300
Oh! Oh!

01:19.800 --> 01:21.467
Have a nice trip, Byrd?

01:21.467 --> 01:23.933
- [ Girls Laughing ]
- Samantha Byrd.

01:23.933 --> 01:27.933
Keep your head up.
Get back in there.

01:27.933 --> 01:29.433
It's no good, Coach.
I'm--

01:29.433 --> 01:32.200
You're a natural, Samantha!

01:32.200 --> 01:34.467
- A natural klutz.
- Now, that's enough of that.

01:34.467 --> 01:37.433
Come on, Byrd.
You're my tallest player.

01:37.433 --> 01:40.100
I need you on my team.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.367
One more time, Anna.

01:42.800 --> 01:45.900
- Go for it, Sam!
- Hey, Cory.

01:45.900 --> 01:47.400
Ball.

01:47.900 --> 01:50.900
- Okay.
- Oops!

01:50.900 --> 01:53.067
[ Coach ]
Come on, Sam! Get into the game!

01:54.000 --> 01:56.567
Why don't you fly away, Byrd?
Take off!

01:56.567 --> 02:00.067
- Give the team a chance.
- All right, Judith. That's enough!

02:00.067 --> 02:02.067
Okay, girls. Back to work!
[ Claps Hands ]

02:02.067 --> 02:05.067
Free throws!
Judith, back to the line.

02:05.067 --> 02:07.067
[ Chattering ]

02:07.067 --> 02:07.787
Ready?

02:09.067 --> 02:11.067
- Here you go, Byrd.
- [ Cory ] Oh, come on, guys.

02:11.067 --> 02:14.267
- Give her a break.
- She stinks!

02:32.100 --> 02:34.133
[ Screams ]

02:34.567 --> 02:36.067
- [ Screaming Continues ]
- Sam!

02:36.500 --> 02:38.800
Oh, my God! Help!

02:38.800 --> 02:41.467
[ Whimpers ]
Cory!

02:41.467 --> 02:43.933
[ Screams ]

02:43.933 --> 02:47.467
- [ Girls Chatter ]
- [ Coach ] Sam, it's okay.

02:47.467 --> 02:49.433
[ Voice Slow, Lower ]
Just relax.

02:49.433 --> 02:52.567
I know you're scared.
Just try to breathe.

02:52.567 --> 02:54.633
You just had the wind
knocked out of you.

02:55.133 --> 02:58.133
For a moment there, I thought
the Byrd was really gonna do it.

02:58.633 --> 03:00.600
- Do what?
- Fly away.

03:00.600 --> 03:03.100
Byrd girl cleared for takeoff.

03:03.100 --> 03:05.533
- Shh!
- Samantha?

03:05.533 --> 03:08.533
[ Kids Chattering, Laughing ]

03:08.533 --> 03:11.433
[ Whispering, Not Audible ]

03:11.433 --> 03:14.433
- [ Girls Laughing ]
- Want to help me strangle Judith?

03:14.433 --> 03:17.800
- Bad idea.
- Why? Give me one good reason.

03:17.800 --> 03:19.600
Your basketball team
will never win another game.

03:19.600 --> 03:23.700
But why does she pick on me?
I did nothing to her.

03:24.100 --> 03:26.433
Don't let her get to you.
Judith is Judith.

03:26.933 --> 03:29.433
I wish--
I don't know what.

03:29.433 --> 03:30.433
[ Girls Laughing Continues ]

03:31.133 --> 03:33.067
The Byrd actually tried to fly today.

03:33.067 --> 03:35.567
She's as clumsy at flying
as she is at basketball.

03:35.567 --> 03:38.033
I tripped because of--

03:38.500 --> 03:41.367
- Nice lip control.
- [ Kids Laughing ]

03:41.367 --> 03:43.467
That is so disgusting.

03:46.800 --> 03:48.300
- [ Clattering ]
- [ Kids Laughing ]

03:48.300 --> 03:50.933
I-I'm really sorry!

03:50.933 --> 03:53.933
[ Laughing Continues ]

03:56.933 --> 03:58.933
[ Boy ]
Ooh.

03:58.933 --> 04:00.933
Hey, Bobby.

04:00.933 --> 04:02.367
[ Bird Cawing ]

04:04.933 --> 04:08.433
- Oh!
- Oh, I'm sorry. I--

04:11.733 --> 04:14.600
- Excuse me.
- I'm really sorry. I--

04:15.200 --> 04:17.632
- I-I didn't see you.
- No.

04:17.632 --> 04:20.399
I'm sorry to have frightened you.

04:20.399 --> 04:21.149
Oh.

04:23.600 --> 04:28.033
There it is.
I have been looking all over for this.

04:28.033 --> 04:31.267
It's yours?
I found it in the gym.

04:31.267 --> 04:34.267
Isn't it amazing how lost objects--

04:34.767 --> 04:37.067
they find their way to strange places?

04:38.500 --> 04:41.433
Really strange.
But if it's yours, here.

04:42.800 --> 04:44.267
Thank you.

04:47.200 --> 04:50.867
Now, maybe you can help me
with something else.

04:50.867 --> 04:54.367
- Can you tell me how to get to Moss Avenue?
- Moss Avenue.

04:54.900 --> 04:57.333
- That's way across town.
- Oh.

04:57.833 --> 05:00.500
How could that have happened?
How could I be so far out of my way?

05:00.500 --> 05:02.000
That happens to me all the time.

05:02.500 --> 05:04.000
It's kind of you to say so,
but I don't believe it.

05:04.500 --> 05:10.000
- Oh, no. Really. It's true.
- Would you mind taking me there?

05:10.500 --> 05:12.500
Gee, I have to get home.

05:13.000 --> 05:14.500
Please.

05:14.500 --> 05:16.500
I'd be so grateful.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.000
If it's not too far out of your way.

05:20.500 --> 05:22.000
Sure.
I guess it's not that far.

05:22.500 --> 05:26.367
You are so kind.
Thank you, uh--

05:26.367 --> 05:28.367
Samantha Byrd.

05:28.867 --> 05:30.867
Thank you, Samantha Byrd.

05:30.867 --> 05:33.867
You may call me Clarissa.

05:34.367 --> 05:36.367
[ Chatters, Indistinct ]

05:39.867 --> 05:41.367
[ Clarissa ]
Oh.

05:41.367 --> 05:44.867
I don't know how
I could have got so lost.

05:45.367 --> 05:48.267
- Ah.
- Are you sure this is where you want to be?

05:49.767 --> 05:52.267
- This is fine.
- Okay, then. Bye.

05:52.700 --> 05:55.133
Wait.
I'd like to give you something...

05:55.633 --> 05:58.100
for being so kind to a stranger.

05:58.100 --> 06:01.200
You don't have to
give me anything, really.

06:01.200 --> 06:04.200
Most young people
wouldn't be so kind.

06:04.200 --> 06:08.733
You must let me repay you.
Please. I insist.

06:09.233 --> 06:14.100
I shall grant you...
three wishes.

06:16.100 --> 06:19.233
Uh, sure.
I mean, that's really cool.

06:19.233 --> 06:22.067
But I don't have any wishes right now.
I've gotta go.

06:22.067 --> 06:25.333
Of course!
I've kept you far too long already.

06:25.833 --> 06:29.267
But understand that
this is no joke, Samantha.

06:29.700 --> 06:32.100
Make your first wish.

06:33.600 --> 06:34.680
Uh, okay.

06:37.100 --> 06:40.667
I wish I was the best player
on the basketball team.

06:40.667 --> 06:43.700
Uh, that's not important.
Really, just forget it.

06:44.167 --> 06:45.600
- I've got to go.
- Wait.

06:46.600 --> 06:48.900
I want you to have this.

06:51.700 --> 06:55.933
And by the way,
your wish will come true.

06:55.933 --> 06:59.433
You will be
the best player on the team.

07:05.100 --> 07:08.033
One, two, three, Mustangs!

07:08.033 --> 07:11.033
- Yeah! Let's go!
- [ Cheering ]

07:12.533 --> 07:14.033
[ Coach ]
Let's do it!

07:14.033 --> 07:15.833
- [ Gasps ]
- [ Grunts ]

07:16.767 --> 07:18.633
Try it again.

07:21.400 --> 07:23.433
[ Coach ]
It's okay, Sam.

07:23.433 --> 07:25.800
[ Kids Cheering ]

07:35.767 --> 07:38.467
[ Coach ]
It's okay! It's all right.

07:42.900 --> 07:45.067
[ Coach ]
Okay!

07:45.067 --> 07:47.567
[ Crowd Groans ]

07:49.567 --> 07:52.067
[ Coach ]
Let's get some points going!

07:54.933 --> 07:57.833
Oh, boy. Okay.
Let's keep it in.

07:58.333 --> 07:59.833
- Come on now.
- [ Buzzer Sounds ]

07:59.833 --> 08:01.433
[ Whistle Blows ]

08:01.433 --> 08:03.900
What is going on out there?

08:04.400 --> 08:06.333
I don't know.
I don't feel so good.

08:06.333 --> 08:09.867
- Anna, how are you feeling?
- Hmm?

08:09.867 --> 08:12.633
[ Kids Cheering ]

08:19.033 --> 08:21.033
[ Coach ]
Come on!

08:22.467 --> 08:25.667
- Throw it to me!
- No, Sam! The other way!

08:25.667 --> 08:28.167
Other way!

08:29.800 --> 08:31.667
Come on, Sam!
Come on!

08:33.567 --> 08:35.100
Try again.

08:35.100 --> 08:37.433
One more time!

08:38.933 --> 08:40.832
- [ Cheering ]
- [ Buzzer Sounds ]

08:40.832 --> 08:42.366
Oh, God.

08:46.867 --> 08:48.367
[ Sighs ]

08:49.367 --> 08:50.700
[ Whooshing ]

08:50.700 --> 08:56.333
Oh! Oh-ho-ho!
[ Laughing ]

08:56.333 --> 08:57.967
- [ Sighs ]
- It was you, wasn't it?

08:57.967 --> 09:00.467
- Oh!
- You made us lose the game.

09:00.467 --> 09:04.600
No! It was your wish.

09:04.600 --> 09:06.767
I just carried it out.

09:06.767 --> 09:10.600
- But I wanted to be the best on the team.
- Oh!

09:10.600 --> 09:13.667
I was the best, all right,
because everyone else was terrible!

09:13.667 --> 09:16.500
Well, wishes are complicated.

09:16.500 --> 09:18.633
Magic isn't an exact science,
you know!

09:18.633 --> 09:21.633
- I mean, I did the best that I could.
- Great.

09:21.633 --> 09:24.933
I know you're upset, Samantha.
That's why I'm here.

09:24.933 --> 09:27.433
The next time...

09:27.433 --> 09:30.067
you must be very careful
what you wish for...

09:30.067 --> 09:33.033
and very clear...

09:33.033 --> 09:35.633
how you phrase it.

09:36.067 --> 09:38.300
- Do you have another wish?
- Not right now, thank you.

09:38.300 --> 09:40.267
I've gotta go.

09:43.533 --> 09:45.533
- [ Man On PA, Indistinct ]
- You found it?

09:46.033 --> 09:49.467
This weird lady said it was hers,
and then she gave it back to you?

09:49.467 --> 09:50.900
Yeah.

09:51.400 --> 09:53.900
- What's your problem?
- Our problem is you.

09:54.400 --> 09:56.867
When are you going to
quit the team?

09:57.867 --> 09:59.367
It's your fault
we lost yesterday.

09:59.867 --> 10:02.100
I didn't see you two
make any great plays.

10:02.100 --> 10:05.367
That's because we spent our time
covering for Byrd brain here.

10:05.367 --> 10:07.367
Just-- Just leave me alone!

10:07.867 --> 10:10.667
I wish everyone
would just buzz off!

10:13.800 --> 10:16.700
- [ Whimpers ]
- [ Buzzing ]

10:21.433 --> 10:23.933
[ Whimpers ]

10:27.367 --> 10:29.067
- [ Buzzing Continues ]
- Cory?

10:29.067 --> 10:30.500
Judith?

10:30.500 --> 10:32.367
Anna!

10:39.033 --> 10:41.033
[ Buzzing ]

10:47.067 --> 10:49.067
Oh!
[ Gasping ]

10:53.733 --> 10:55.933
Please, is--
is anybody here?

10:55.933 --> 10:59.933
I-- I didn't mean it!
Really, I'm sorry!

11:03.000 --> 11:06.000
Mr. Johnson! Oh!

11:06.000 --> 11:06.750
Oh!

11:13.200 --> 11:15.167
[ Loud Buzzing ]

11:19.900 --> 11:20.650
No!

11:28.367 --> 11:29.687
[ Buzzing ]

11:44.533 --> 11:47.033
[ Loud Buzzing ]

11:50.033 --> 11:52.533
I didn't mean it, Clarissa!

11:52.533 --> 11:54.533
Not everyone!

11:56.467 --> 11:58.467
Hello! Anybody there?

11:58.467 --> 12:00.633
- Please!
- [ Screeching ]

12:01.600 --> 12:03.600
Clarissa!

12:03.600 --> 12:05.600
[ Upbeat ]

12:09.667 --> 12:10.387
Bobby!

12:13.500 --> 12:14.900
Mom! Dad!

12:14.900 --> 12:17.167
[ Door Opens ]

12:17.167 --> 12:18.600
[ Door Closes ]

12:19.867 --> 12:22.967
No! Don't!
That's my mom or my dad!

12:23.467 --> 12:24.467
Oh!
[ Gasps ]

12:25.167 --> 12:27.100
- My goodness.
- [ Buzzing ]

12:27.100 --> 12:27.820
Sorry.

12:29.600 --> 12:31.100
[ Exhales ]
Look what you've done.

12:31.100 --> 12:34.467
I knew you'd be unhappy
with your wish.

12:34.467 --> 12:38.033
It's all Judith's fault.
If she weren't so mean--

12:39.033 --> 12:41.433
I never meant to
turn anyone into a fly.

12:41.433 --> 12:45.033
I know,
but remember what you said.

12:46.400 --> 12:48.367
- Buzz off?
- Mm-hmm.

12:48.367 --> 12:52.367
I followed your instructions
as best I could.

12:52.867 --> 12:56.033
- I do have some powers, Sam--
- [ Buzzing ]

12:57.033 --> 13:00.000
I'm not a mind reader.

13:00.000 --> 13:01.900
I do as I'm asked.

13:02.900 --> 13:05.300
But what good is a wish
if it always backfires?

13:05.300 --> 13:07.300
They don't always backfire.

13:08.767 --> 13:12.267
Anyway,
you still have one more wish.

13:12.267 --> 13:14.767
Only you must be careful.

13:14.767 --> 13:16.600
This is your last wish.

13:20.600 --> 13:22.633
- I wish--
- Ah, ah!

13:24.100 --> 13:28.567
Right.
I have to get this one right.

13:28.567 --> 13:30.767
Take your time.

13:32.267 --> 13:34.767
[ Buzzing Continues ]

13:39.267 --> 13:42.267
[ Snoring ]

13:45.133 --> 13:46.633
- [ Snores ]
- Okay!

13:46.633 --> 13:50.033
- I've got my wish.
- There.

13:50.033 --> 13:52.367
Tell me your wish.

13:52.867 --> 13:55.267
I wish everything
to go back to normal--

13:55.267 --> 13:58.767
the way it was before the flies--

13:58.767 --> 14:02.033
except I want Judith to be my friend.

14:03.533 --> 14:05.200
- All right.
- No, wait!

14:06.700 --> 14:09.533
I want Judith to think
I'm the greatest.

14:16.033 --> 14:18.067
I understand.

14:18.567 --> 14:20.767
[ Whooshing ]

14:25.833 --> 14:28.067
- Who are you talking to, honey?
- Is Dad okay?

14:28.067 --> 14:30.033
Of course.
He's in the living room.

14:31.767 --> 14:34.267
[ Phone Rings ]

14:35.767 --> 14:38.667
Hello?
One moment, please.

14:38.667 --> 14:40.667
Someone by the name of Judith.

14:42.300 --> 14:44.800
[ Chattering ]

14:45.800 --> 14:48.300
Sam! Over here.

14:50.800 --> 14:53.300
How do you like it?
I made it just for you.

14:53.300 --> 14:54.800
It's good.

14:54.800 --> 14:57.300
- And how do you like this?
- Great.

14:57.300 --> 14:59.200
It's just like yours.

14:59.200 --> 15:01.533
Come on, ladies.
We've got a lot of work to do!

15:01.533 --> 15:03.867
Sam? Judith?

15:03.867 --> 15:06.767
What are you waiting for?
Hustle up now.

15:08.967 --> 15:12.333
Oh, here.
Let me get you a clean uniform.

15:15.233 --> 15:17.667
Hello.
It doesn't matter what Byrd wears.

15:18.100 --> 15:20.033
She's a walking catastrophe.

15:20.500 --> 15:22.400
And what have you done
with your hair?

15:22.400 --> 15:25.433
Don't you love it?
It's just like Sam's!

15:25.433 --> 15:27.033
Anybody home?

15:28.567 --> 15:31.000
- [ All ] Defense!
- Can you help me?

15:31.000 --> 15:34.167
- [ Coach ] The other way.
- Me, help you?

15:34.167 --> 15:37.000
You're a natural.
Show me how you do it.

15:37.000 --> 15:38.500
[ Coach ]
Shake it out. All right.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.000
Okay. Sure.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.000
Get low!

15:42.500 --> 15:43.833
- [ Girls Shouts ]
- To this side.

15:45.067 --> 15:49.000
The other way.
That's it, that's it.

15:49.500 --> 15:53.000
Tough break.
That's how I want to learn to shoot.

15:53.500 --> 15:55.200
[ Coach ]
Good. Back!

15:55.200 --> 15:57.133
[ Girls ]
Defense!

15:57.633 --> 15:59.633
[ Man On PA, Indistinct ]

15:59.633 --> 16:03.633
- What are you gonna have?
- I don't know. What are you gonna have?

16:03.633 --> 16:06.133
Whatever you have.
You have such great taste.

16:06.633 --> 16:08.633
[ Chattering ]

16:09.633 --> 16:12.133
And maybe on the weekend,
we can go shopping.

16:12.633 --> 16:14.533
I mean, you have to tell me
where you get your shoes.

16:16.033 --> 16:18.233
They're just your basic shoes.

16:18.233 --> 16:20.133
But I love the color.

16:20.133 --> 16:22.133
Yeah. Basic black.

16:22.133 --> 16:25.267
Have you ever noticed how Sam
has the coolest colored pencils?

16:25.267 --> 16:27.400
I was just going to say.

16:27.833 --> 16:31.867
She can do so much with
your eight basic colors.

16:32.833 --> 16:35.267
- Sam, can I talk to you?
- Sure.

16:35.267 --> 16:38.267
- Alone.
- Oh, hey, sure.

16:38.767 --> 16:40.900
Uh, listen, Sam.
I'll talk to you later.

16:40.900 --> 16:42.400
Maybe we can study
together tonight?

16:42.900 --> 16:45.633
Uh, I think I'll be busy.
Sorry.

16:45.633 --> 16:47.633
That's cool.
Whatever.

16:48.133 --> 16:48.853
Later.

16:52.633 --> 16:55.000
- What's going on?
- What's up with her?

16:55.000 --> 16:59.000
You wouldn't believe it.
It's m-- my--

16:59.000 --> 17:00.867
It must have been something I said.

17:00.867 --> 17:02.933
Ugh.
It feels like something I ate.

17:04.933 --> 17:06.633
Well, what do I do?

17:07.133 --> 17:11.133
Well, if your old worst enemy
is your new best friend,

17:11.133 --> 17:13.067
shouldn't you be happier?

17:17.700 --> 17:19.700
[ Rewinding, Beeps ]

17:19.700 --> 17:21.200
Hi, Sam. It's Judith.

17:21.200 --> 17:24.200
You're not in,
so I guess I'll call you later.

17:24.200 --> 17:26.700
Hi! It's Judith again!
Call me when you get in.

17:26.700 --> 17:30.200
Hey, where are you? It's Judith.
Call me.  - [ Phone Rings ]

17:30.200 --> 17:32.933
[ On Tape ]
Hi. It's Judith. I'll call you later.

17:33.367 --> 17:35.867
- [ Ringing ]
- Sam, it's Judith. I hope you're okay.

17:41.867 --> 17:43.800
[ Sighs ]

17:45.200 --> 17:47.200
[ Clicks ]

17:49.200 --> 17:52.833
- [ Gasps ]
- Shh! It's just me, Judith.

17:52.833 --> 17:55.500
What--
What are you doing here?

17:55.500 --> 17:58.000
I snuck in and hid in your closet.

17:58.000 --> 18:00.467
- What, are you nuts?
- You said we could study together later.

18:00.467 --> 18:03.467
Not tonight.
It's way too late!

18:03.467 --> 18:05.467
[ Mom ] Sam?
Are you talking on the phone?

18:05.467 --> 18:07.033
No, Mom. It's okay.

18:07.533 --> 18:10.033
You know you're not allowed
on the phone after lights out.

18:10.033 --> 18:11.967
Yeah.
Good night, Mom.

18:13.400 --> 18:15.233
I just love your room.

18:15.233 --> 18:18.667
- These sheets are so cool.
- Shut up!

18:19.167 --> 18:20.167
You have to be completely quiet

18:20.167 --> 18:22.467
until I can find a way
to get you out of here.

18:22.467 --> 18:25.600
- [ Whispers ] Sorry.
- [ Sighs ]

18:25.600 --> 18:30.100
[ Man On TV ] The forecast:
mostly sunny skies today.

18:30.100 --> 18:32.067
Bye, Mom.
I'll see you after school.

18:32.067 --> 18:34.567
- [ Mom ] Have a good day, dear.
- Hi!

18:34.567 --> 18:36.567
[ Groans ]

18:36.567 --> 18:38.067
I thought maybe we could
walk to school together.

18:38.567 --> 18:40.067
No!

18:40.567 --> 18:43.533
Sam! Wait! What's the matter?
I thought we were best friends!

18:48.033 --> 18:49.533
Short cut.

18:49.533 --> 18:52.967
- Stop bothering me!
- What do you mean?

18:52.967 --> 18:55.300
- [ Bird Cawing ]
- [ Whooshing ]

18:56.767 --> 18:58.167
- Oh!
- Oh! Oh!

18:58.167 --> 18:59.900
- Oh. Uh--
- You!

